parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Warped rear brake rotors can cause the brakes to lock up, leading to sudden slowing or loss of control, which can result in accidents or near-misses.
symptoms: Rear brake rotor warping
brake shuttering or vibrating when using the rear brakes
brake pads wearing out prematurely.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Brake Fluid Leaks and Premature Brake Pad Wear
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Brake fluid leaks can cause brake pads to wear out prematurely, leading to reduced braking performance and increased risk of accidents.
symptoms: Brake pads need to be replaced frequently
brake fluid leaking onto brake pads and wheels
poor gas mileage.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The stalling and hesitation of the motorcycle at low speeds can cause loss of control, accidents, and potentially lead to injuries or fatalities, especially when riding a heavy vehicle.
symptoms: The motorcycle stalls or hesitates when accelerating from a low speed (1-10 mph)

often requiring the rider to engage the clutch and throttle to regain power; the issue is more frequent when the engine is cold or after a short stop; the motorcycle may surge forward rapidly after hesitating.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the anti-dive device can cause the motorcycle to experience uneven handling, leading to a loss of control, accidents, or injuries, especially during braking or sudden maneuvers.
symptoms: The motorcycle experiences bumps or jolts while riding
especially during braking or sudden turns
the front end of the motorcycle dives or drops excessively
the motorcycle's handling feels unstable or unresponsive.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Engine Stuttering and Stalling at Low Speeds
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The engine stuttering and stalling at low speeds can cause the vehicle to lose forward momentum, leading to a loss of control and potentially resulting in accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The engine stutters or hesitates
the engine stalls
the vehicle is unable to maintain forward momentum
the vehicle requires emergency action to regain control
such as quickly disengaging the clutch to coast to a safe stop.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The engine stalling while warming up can cause the motorcycle to lose power and potentially crash, especially if the rider is in the middle of a turn, which can lead to accidents and injuries.
symptoms: The engine stalls while the motorcycle is being ridden during the warm-up period
requiring the rider to pull the clutch to regain control
the motorcycle loses power
the motorcycle crashes if the stall occurs during a turn.
